\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing actor versioning issues**\\n\\nIf the existing version has actor 1.1.5, which is deterministic but incorrect, adding 2.0.0-M1 might lead to duplicates. I'm wondering if the driver could update the dependencies before generation. If build.gradle has fixed dependencies, the driver can add testImplementation. Duplicates could lead to Gradle conflict resolution picking 2.0.0-M1, while the scala-reflect versions may vary. There could be an issue with missing classes due to removals, and potential incompatibility between actor 1.1.5 and 2.0.0-M1 due to LogHelper dependencies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Determining library setup requirements**\\n\\nI'm realizing that we need extra setup and not necessarily just updating existing pinned dependencies. The driver can add dependencies deterministically, but maybe the agent can handle that as well. I’m considering whether the library needs additional setup beyond the usual generated test scaffold for achieving meaningful coverage. I think concrete evidence, like the provided POM dependencies, would help clarify what needs to be done before we can effectively test and cover everything properly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_1DZ9T7p42REvM3zINakYPc6m|fc_0d1a8476dfa7a787016a42ff0d7968819797ec766773c1e7b9", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "cd /home/vjovanov/tmp/pekko-research-8878 && curl -fsSLO https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/scala-lang/scala-library/2.13.18/scala-library-2.13.18.jar && cat > /home/vjovanov/tmp/pekko-research-8878/Load.java <<'JAVA'\npublic class Load { public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception { for (String c: args) { System.out.println(c); System.out.println(Class.forName(c)); } } }\nJAVA\njavac Load.java && java -cp .:pekko-parsing_2.13-2.0.0-M1.jar:scala-library-2.13.18.jar Load org.apache.pekko.macros.LogHelper org.apache.pekko.macros.LogHelperMacro", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-